<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6706263-cylia-kamp"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1319040295i/6706263._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6706263-cylia-kamp">Cylia Kamp</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This response is probably way too late, but I just noticed the question today when I was moving some of my reviews to my personal computer. Anyway the<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This response is probably way too late, but I just noticed the question today when I was moving some of my reviews to my personal computer. Anyway the explanation of the translation of "mbele ache" can be found on page 271. Also Alice Walker signs the author's note with "mbele ache" on page 283.<br /><br />Sincerely, Celeste<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
