<div id="review_1021842735" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1021842735" />
    <a title="Cylia Kamp" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6706263-cylia-kamp"><img alt="Cylia Kamp" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1319040295p2/6706263.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1021842735?book_show_action=true">Aug 09, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cylia Kamp" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cylia Kamp" href="/user/show/6706263-cylia-kamp">Cylia Kamp</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781595583642" href="/book/show/2761997-possessing-the-secret-of-joy">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6706263-cylia-kamp?shelf=my-written-reviews">my-written-reviews</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1021842735" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17079912728080279745">In 1991 Alice Walker first published the novel, <i>Possessing the Secret of Joy</i>. It introduced many readers to the ruthless, painful technique known as female genital mutilation (FMG) or female circumcision, suffered by 90 to 100 million women worldwide. Because the subject had long been taboo among those groups who practice it as well as throughout the rest of the world, the book was taken out of print. But fortunately for modern readers and current sufferers everywhere, Ms. Walker and others bega</span>
  <span id="freeText17079912728080279745" style="display:none">In 1991 Alice Walker first published the novel, <i>Possessing the Secret of Joy</i>. It introduced many readers to the ruthless, painful technique known as female genital mutilation (FMG) or female circumcision, suffered by 90 to 100 million women worldwide. Because the subject had long been taboo among those groups who practice it as well as throughout the rest of the world, the book was taken out of print. But fortunately for modern readers and current sufferers everywhere, Ms. Walker and others began to report even more thoroughly on the noxious anti-feminism and unusual folklore supporting the practice. Their actions and appeals resulted in the reissue of <i>Possessing the Secret of Joy</i> in 2008. Another factor driving the need for more information about FMG was the increasing numbers of immigrants crossing the US borders. Many were suffering from the consequences of the procedure. Physicians and staff running the US clinics which serve this population were soon in need of better treatment information. Thank goodness other books and conferences began popping up, and the horrors (both physical and psychological) and the treatments of the practice have been further revealed.<br /><br />I highly recommend this novel not only for its information but also for its startling truth and dramatic storytelling. Be aware, though, presentation of the details of the procedure and its possible consequences are not sugar coated.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17079912728080279745" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


